issue.body:
Signed-off-by: Igor Bezukh <ibezukh@redhat.com>

Runbook PR: https://github.com/openshift/runbooks/pull/318

**What this PR does / why we need it**:
In an upgrade scenario it can happen that duplicate wasp-agent
deployment can appear, since previous wasp-agent deployments
were manual and in a different namespace.
Therefore in order to make sure the user is aware of it we
are adding an alert which will rely on the a metric of memory
overcommit percentage and presence of wasp namespace.

pull_request.title: Fix auth flow: popup signin, profile creation, email resend
pull_request.body:
## Purpose

Based on user feedback, this PR addresses several authentication issues:
- Users experiencing "page unavailable" errors when signing in via redirect
- Missing user profile creation in Supabase backend table
- Email confirmation not being received after signup
- Need for automatic dashboard redirect for authenticated Gmail users
- Rate limiting issues with Supabase free tier email sending

## Code changes

### Authentication Flow Improvements
- **Popup-based Google OAuth**: Changed from redirect to popup flow to prevent "page unavailable" errors
- **Automatic profile creation**: Added logic to create user profiles in Supabase when they don't exist
- **Auto-redirect for authenticated users**: HomePage now automatically redirects logged-in users to dashboard

### Email Confirmation Enhancements
- **Success toast notifications**: Added toast messages for successful email signup
- **Resend confirmation feature**: New `resendConfirmation` function and UI button for users who didn't receive emails
- **Better error handling**: Improved error messages for email confirmation and rate limiting issues

### UI/UX Improvements
- **Loading states**: Added proper loading handling in ProtectedRoute
- **Toast system**: Integrated Sonner toast notifications throughout the app
- **Conditional resend button**: Shows resend option when email confirmation is needed

### Technical Details
- Modified `AuthContext.tsx` to handle popup OAuth flow and profile creation
- Updated `AuthModal.tsx` with resend confirmation functionality
- Added toast notifications in `main.tsx`
- Enhanced error handling for various auth scenarios

performed_via_github_app.description:
Publish incredibly high performance websites and applications right from GitHub. The Netlify platform connects your repositories to an all-in-one workflow for global CDN deployment, continuous integration, and automatic (and free) HTTPS. Each time you commit changes, Netlify builds your site, prerenders markup, and optimizes assets on dedicated build infrastructure. Easily create an entirely automated workflows for your web applications

## Features

### Push your site live, directly from GitHub
Deploy your site to an ultra-redundant global CDN that’s purpose built for serving pages and assets quickly and consistently.

### Automate deployment
Netlify’s built-in Continuous Deployment automatically runs your build commands and deploys the result whenever you push to your Git repository.

### Add a custom domain
Purchase domains and manage DNS zones and records right inside of Netlify.

### HTTPS is automatic
Your site will automatically be secured with a free TLS certificate from Let’s Encrypt.

### Deploy Previews
Netlify’s Deploy Previews streamlined your workflow by giving you a unique, permanent URL to check what your changes will be like in production whenever you submit a pull request.

### And a lot more!
Netlify includes solutions for forms, identity, and even custom functions powered by AWS Lambda. And all this functionality can be configured directly in your repo.

pull_request.title: opencl: mark `argsort` unsupported if cols exceed workgroup limit
pull_request.body: In the current implementation, the workgroup size is `(cols, 1, 1)`. For large tensors, the workgroup size may exceed the kernel limit, resulting in kernel launch failure. This PR marks such `argsort` as unsupported. Also print out the max workgroup size supported by the device (the upper bound of the max workgroup size supported by a particular kernel) for reference.

Introduce IndexChunkedSet

* Changes:

- Introduce IndexChunkedSet, complete with chunk iteration.
- Implement all set tests for IndexChunkedSet.

* Motivation:

IndexChunkedSet takes advantages of chunks to implement faster set
functionalities, notably bitwise operators.

Fix inconsistency between try_fold & try_fold_before/after

* Changes:

- Exclude "initial" index in try_fold_before/after default
  implementations.
- Adjust tests.
- Adjust implementation of BTreeSet to match.

* Motivation:

It's easy for the caller to call `f` on the initial element on their
own, but impossible for the caller to have the implementation NOT call
it.

CRITICAL: Remove all mock data and fix LangSmith URLs

- Remove all mock data fallbacks from dataService.js
- Fix LangSmith URL structure (remove incorrect /projects/p/ path)
- Add proper error handling when API is unavailable
- Dashboard now requires real API connection - no mock data ever
- LangSmith URLs now use correct format: /o/{org_id} instead of /o/{org_id}/projects/p/{project}

Changes:
- dataService.js: Removed getMockVirtuousCycleData, getMockHealthData, getMockDashboardData
- App.jsx: Added proper error state when no real data available
- langsmithService.js: Fixed URL structure for LangSmith links

This ensures dashboard only shows real data from tilores_X API and LangSmith.
